+# Sale Core E2E Verifier — Plan
+
+**Filed:** 2026-05-24 (autonomous Track 7)
+**Author:** Claude Sonnet 4.6
+**Status:** Plan only. No verifier script in this PR.
+
+Plans a non-prod end-to-end verifier covering the full `/sale` admin
+flow. Boss UI smoke remains the authoritative production verification,
+but a deterministic e2e script reduces regression surface between Boss
+smokes.
+
+Existing verifiers in `scripts/`:
+- `verify-sale-quick-bulk-product-codes.ts` — Tier 3.8
+- `verify-sale-d4-d6-functional-flow.ts` — sale D4/D6 functional flow
+- `verify-booking-flow.ts` — booking lifecycle
+- `verify-booking-conversion.ts` — booking → order
+- `verify-booking-create.ts` — manual create
+- `verify-order-reservation-cleanup.ts` — stock cleanup
+- `verify-expire-reservations-cron.ts` — reservation TTL
+- `verify-inventory-bulk-product-codes.ts` — Tier 3.9-D2-C
+
+This proposed `verify-sale-core-e2e.ts` would compose pieces from the
+above into one coherent admin journey.
+
+---
+
+## 1. Scope
+
+Single deterministic script covering admin's typical day:
+
+1. Create products in inventory (single + bulk)
+2. Attach products to a saleDate (sale-side)
+3. Create bookings (manual + multi-code)
+4. Mutate bookings (confirm, cancel)
+5. Create order from confirmed bookings
+6. Compute summary (totals + per-status counts)
+7. Inventory bulk re-create same codes (test reuse-or-create)
+8. Cleanup
+
+**Non-goals:**
+- Webhook delivery (Tier 4.1)
+- Outbound messaging (Tier 4.5+)
+- Payment flow
+- Image upload
+- Authentication (verifier runs at repository layer; HTTP route auth covered by unit tests)
+
+---
+
+## 2. Production-safety guard (same 6 layers)
+
+```ts
+import { evaluateNonProdDatabase } from './lib/non-prod-db-guard';
+```
+
+Existing `evaluateNonProdDatabase` enforces:
+1. CONFIRM_NON_PROD_DB=true required
+2. DATABASE_URL must be set
+3. Hostname must be `localhost` or `127.0.0.1`
+4. Hostname must not match production deny-list (`junction.proxy.rlwy.net`, `rlwy.net`)
+5. URL must not contain `nazhahatyai`
+6. DB name must equal `liveshop_pro`
+
+Exit `2` on guard failure. `--help` + `--preflight` flags per
+inventory verifier pattern (Track 2).
+
+**NEVER** soften the guard for any verifier.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Proposed test cases (15 cases)
+
+### A — Inventory side
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| A1 | Create single inventory product | Product + Variant exists, 0 BroadcastProduct |
+| A2 | Create bulk inventory products 1..5 | 5 Product + 5 Variant, 0 BroadcastProduct, atomic |
+| A3 | Reuse-or-create: same codes again | productCreated=false, no new rows |
+
+### B — Sale side: attach + bookings
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| B1 | Sale quick-create product code (Tier 3.8) | Product + Variant + BroadcastProduct trio |
+| B2 | AddFromStock batch attaches existing inventory to today | New BroadcastProduct rows reusing existing Product + Variant |
+| B3 | Manual create booking (PENDING_REVIEW) | Booking row with status PENDING_REVIEW, 0 reservations |
+| B4 | Multi-code booking (future Phase 1.5-D) | Skipped — held |
+
+### C — Booking lifecycle
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| C1 | Confirm PENDING booking → CONFIRMED + reservation | StockReservation row created in same tx |
+| C2 | Cancel CONFIRMED booking → CANCELLED + reservation released | releasedAt set |
+| C3 | Cancel PENDING booking → CANCELLED, no reservation touched | No StockReservation activity |
+| C4 | Idempotent confirm replay | Returns { idempotent: true } |
+| C5 | Idempotent cancel replay | Returns { idempotent: true, stockReleased: false } |
+| C6 | Confirm with insufficient stock | Throws INSUFFICIENT_STOCK, status stays PENDING |
+
+### D — Order conversion
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| D1 | Convert N CONFIRMED bookings → Order | Booking.convertedOrderId set; all reservations released; OrderItem groupBy correct |
+| D2 | Idempotent convert replay | Returns existing Order |
+| D3 | Convert with mixed status (1 PENDING + 1 CONFIRMED) | Throws BOOKING_INVALID_STATUS, no Order created |
+
+### E — Summary
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| E1 | Summary for active saleDate | totalBookings + per-status counts correct |
+| E2 | Summary range mode | days[] in order, top-level totals = sum |
+| E3 | Summary empty saleDate | broadcastProductCount=0, panel shows empty state |
+
+### F — Cleanup
+
+| Case | Description | Asserts |
+|---|---|---|
+| F1 | All fixtures removed | Final count of Shop/User/Product/Variant/BP/Booking/Order/Reservation = 0 |
+
+---
+
+## 4. Implementation plan
+
+If Boss approves, implement as `scripts/verify-sale-core-e2e.ts`:
+
+```
+scripts/verify-sale-core-e2e.ts (~600 LOC)
+├── assertNonProdDatabase() — same 6-layer guard
+├── HELP_TEXT — usage
+├── --help + --preflight flags
+├── Fixture setup (Shop, User, ShopMember, Category)
+├── Cases A1-A3 (inventory)
+├── Cases B1-B3 (sale attach + bookings)
+├── Cases C1-C6 (booking lifecycle)
+├── Cases D1-D3 (order conversion)
+├── Cases E1-E3 (summary)
+├── Cleanup F1
+└── Summary report (PASS/FAIL/TOTAL)
+```
+
+Exit codes:
+- `0` — all 15 PASS + cleanup OK
+- `1` — any case fail
+- `2` — guard blocked
+
+npm script:
+```json
+"verify:sale:core-e2e": "tsx scripts/verify-sale-core-e2e.ts"
+```
+
+---
+
+## 5. Why NOT implement now
+
+The autonomous block has Boss policy "If Docker/DB uncertainty would
+cause churn, skip and document":
+
+1. Docker host→DB auth quirk documented in Track 2 still applies
+2. Existing 8 verifiers already cover most cases independently:
+   - A1-A3 → `verify-inventory-bulk-product-codes.ts`
+   - B1 → `verify-sale-quick-bulk-product-codes.ts`
+   - B3 → `verify-booking-create.ts`
+   - C1-C2 → `verify-booking-flow.ts`
+   - C2 stock release → `verify-order-reservation-cleanup.ts`
+   - D1-D3 → `verify-booking-conversion.ts`
+   - E1-E3 → not yet covered by any verifier (gap)
+3. Boss UI smoke is the authoritative path
+4. A single 600 LOC verifier introduces coordination risk vs 8 focused ones
+
+**Recommendation:** defer implementation. If implemented later, extract
+shared fixture setup helper to `scripts/lib/sale-core-fixtures.ts`
+first to reduce duplication.
+
+---
+
+## 6. Alternative: incremental fill-the-gap
+
+Rather than 600 LOC mega-verifier, write smallest missing pieces:
+
+| Gap | Suggested verifier | Effort |
+|---|---|---|
+| Summary single-day | `verify-sale-summary-single.ts` | ~150 LOC |
+| Summary range | `verify-sale-summary-range.ts` | ~200 LOC |
+| AddFromStock batch | `verify-sale-add-from-stock.ts` | ~180 LOC |
+
+Each its own PR, its own 6-layer guard wrapper, easier to review and
+maintain. Recommended over mega-verifier.
+
+---
+
+## 7. CI considerations
+
+Verifiers are **NOT** run in CI (no postgres service container in
+GitHub Actions). They remain manual-run scripts for:
+- Developer local validation
+- Pre-deploy gate (Boss-run on stable machine)
+- Post-migration smoke
+
+If future CI gains a postgres service, a verifier subset (cleanup-safe
++ deterministic + < 30s) could become CI gate. Out of scope for this
+plan.
+
