+## 9. Hard rules (when implementing)
+
+- ❌ NEVER soften the 6-layer guard
+- ❌ NEVER use production credentials
+- ❌ NEVER skip cleanup on FAIL (leak fixtures)
+- ❌ NEVER assert positive cases without negative-case coverage
+- ❌ NEVER hardcode date strings — derive from runId for determinism
+- ✅ ALWAYS print sanitized URL (password masked)
+- ✅ ALWAYS support `--preflight` for guard-only check
+- ✅ ALWAYS bound runtime (target ≤ 60s total)
+- ✅ ALWAYS use same RunId pattern as inventory verifier for cleanup safety
